                    "id" : "introduction",
                    "text" : [ { "text" : "### Introduction\n\nWhen we are born, we cannot walk and must be carried in our parents' arms. Over time, we begin to crawl, take our first steps, and eventually learn to run. The process of learning follows a similar progression: we start with the basics and, gradually, move on to more complex concepts. In this text, we will explore the first steps of this journey in both reading and *pre-mathematics*, focusing on addition",
                                 "source" : [ 
                                              { "type": 1,
                                                "uuid": "d6a6b284-a060-4a85-bc6c-9d2fe442254c",
                                                "text": "González Redondo, Francisco A., 00:08:20",
                                                "date" :  {"type" : "gregory", "year" : "2024", "month" : "-1", "day" : "-1" }}
                                 ],
                                 "isTable" : false,
